<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

<ul>
  <li><a href="#GetFreeBSD">Where Can I Get the Operating System?</a></li>
  <li><a href="#FreeBSDQuestion">I Have a FreeBSD Question.</a></li>
  <li><a href="#Volunteer">How Can I Volunteer?</a></li>
  <li><a href="#DonateHardware">How Can I Donate Some Hardware?</a></li>
  <li><a href="#TravelGrant">How Can I Apply For a Travel Grant?</a></li>
  <li><a href="#FreeBSDTrademarkPermission">How Can I Get Permission to Use The FreeBSD Trademarks?</a></li>
  <li><a href="#LogoOnDonorsPage">How Do I Get My Logo on the Donors Page?</a></li>
</ul>

<h2><a id="GetFreeBSD">Where can I get the Operating System?</a></h2>
<p>
  To get your own copy of FreeBSD go to the project's website to find out how
  to download or purchase the OS.  Click
  <a href="http://www.freebsd.org/where.html">here</a> to find out more about
  getting FreeBSD.
</p>

<h2><a id="FreeBSDQuestion">I Have a FreeBSD Question.</a></h2>
<p>
  Do you have a question related to FreeBSD and you don't know where to get
  the answer? You can send a question to freebsd-questions@freebsd.org. Or, you
  can go to
  <a href="http://www.freebsd.org/support.html">http://www.freebsd.org/support.html</a>
  to find out how to get support.
</p>

<h2><a id="Volunteer">How Can I Volunteer on the Project?</a></h2>
<p>
  We receive many emails from people who would like to volunteer on the
  project. Click
  <a href="http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/articles/contributing/index.html">here</a>
  to find out how you can contribute to the FreeBSD Project.
</p>

<h2><a id="DonateHardware">How Can I Donate Some Hardware?</a></h2>
<p>
  So, you have hardware you'd like to donate to the Project. First, we'd like
  to say THANK YOU! The Project handles all hardware donations. They also keep
  a <a href="http://www.freebsd.org/donations/wantlist.html">developer's wish list</a>,
  so you can see who wants what. Go to
  <a href="http://www.freebsd.org/donations/">http://www.freebsd.org/donations/</a>
  to find how to donate your hardware.
</p>

<h2><a id="TravelGrant">How Can I Apply For a Travel Grant?</a></h2>
<p>
  We support FreeBSD developers with their travel expenses to attend FreeBSD
  related conferences. To apply just fill out a
  <a href="http://www.freebsdfoundation.org/documents/TravelRequestForm.pdf">Travel Grant Application</a>.
  Make sure you review the Travel Policy on the application before filling out.
  Also, it is very important that you include a detailed justification on why
  attending this conference will benefit the FreeBSD Project and community.
</p>

<h2><a id="FreeBSDTrademarkPermission">How Can I Get Permission to Use The FreeBSD Trademarks?</a></h2>
<p>
  The Foundation owns the trademarks for the mark FreeBSD, the FreeBSD logo,
  and "Powered by FreeBSD." If you would like permission to use any of these
  trademarks, please review our <a
  href="http://www.freebsdfoundation.org/documents/Guidelines">
  Trademark Usage Terms and Conditions</a>.  After reading the document, you
  may send an email stating you have read and agree to the document to
  trademark@freebsdfoundation.org. Please include how you plan on using the
  trademarks. You may be requested to submit artwork for the foundation to
  review.
</p>

<h2><a id="LogoOnDonorsPage">How Do I Get My Logo on the Donors Page?</a></h2>
<p>
  We would love to include your logo on our website. When you donate $10,000
  or more, we will gladly include your 128x100 color logo on our
  <a href="http://www.freebsdfoundation.org/donate/sponsors">Donors Page</a>.
</p>


